LISH, with a score of 40.0% and PARTIAL ALIGNMENT among the timeframes.\n\n## PREDICTION\n**NYSE SESSION SIDE: BUY SIDE**\n\n| Instrument | Direction | Confidence | Level |\n|------------|-----------|------------|-------|\n| NQ (Nasdaq-100) | BULLISH | 60% | MEDIUM |\n\n**NQ Prediction: BULLISH**\n**Confidence: 60% \u2014 MEDIUM**\n\n## TOP REASONS\n1. The mixed news sentiment, with a focus on AI optimism, supports a bullish bias for tech and growth stocks.\n2. The macro environment, with a slightly weaker dollar and lower yields, is supportive of the NQ.\n3. The multi-TF structure, although not fully aligned, shows a leaning towards the bullish side on key timeframes.\n\n## KEY RISKS\n- Geopolitical tensions, especially US-Iran relations, could escalate and negatively impact the market.\n- Inflation concerns and interest rate fears could resurface, pressuring tech and growth stocks.\n\n## WHAT TO WATCH DURING NYSE SESSION\n- Any developments in US-Iran relations and their potential impact on the market.\n- Key NQ price levels, such as the previous day's high and low, and any significant round numbers.\n- Economic data releases, although none are scheduled for the NYSE session, any unexpected announcements could move the market.\n\n## ONE-LINE SUMMARY\n\"2026-06-02 NYSE SESSION: BUY SIDE \u2014 AI optimism and a supportive macro environment lean the bias towards the upside for NQ, despite mixed news sentiment and geopolitical risks.\"",
